overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking to validate its adherence to the provided Statement of
  Work and detailed questionnaire specification. The agent performed an in-depth
  analysis, identifying several critical gaps and areas for enhancement.
  Subsequently, the agent systematically implemented these missing features.
  This included adding a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness with crucial safety
  messaging, integrating detection logic for Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea
  (COMISA) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and implementing a weighted scoring
  system for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS). Furthermore, the agent expanded
  the CSV export functionality to encompass all questionnaire responses,
  introduced new questions for pain severity and chronic fatigue screening, and
  incorporated sections for medical and mental health history. The approach
  involved updating types, validation schemas, and UI components, ensuring a
  robust and compliant application.
